node.text: Why do we believe good musicians, artists, creatives are automatically “good” people.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by مريم حسنا on July 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Make sure you are preparing internally for what you are manifesting externally. -maryam hasnaa'.

node.text:
You created your vision board but did you prepare your nervous system for what you are calling in? 

So that you are in a position to actually be open, present and fully available in your body to be able to receive it when it actually shows. It’s one thing to play it out in your mind and totally different when it’s embodied. 

Many of us are actually really good manifestors but also highly sensitive and have a difficult time being in our body. That means that even the things we want can feel overwhelming. Especially when it comes to relationships. Often other people are simultaneously our greatest source of joy and anguish. 

I’m hoping I can shed some light on this topic next month as we begin out class series on The Highly Sensitive Intuitive in Relationships.

Are you constantly the one experiencing telepathy with the other person? Do you pick up on behaviors and even games the other person is playing before they even know they are playing them. Are you constantly knowing things but feel a bit crazy sharing them because you don’t know how you know. Are you always getting intuitive messages and questioning your own hunches because the other person can not relate to how tuned In you are. Do you feel uncomfortable with all of the information you are receiving because you actually don’t even know how to talk about what you’re feeling? I mean I could go on and on. 

This dilemma is an integral part of this growth period many of us are in because the templates for relationships itself is actually changing. Instead of the exact thing we want being scary or overwhelming we can absolutely prepare our own body, mind, bio-field to fully show up for the experience we want. And the best part we don’t have to change who we are or become less Sensitive. Our sensitivity deserves to be respected, honored, even revered, in our relationships. 

I’m excited to share these templates. You can drop in for a class any time at @newearthmysteryschool. You are also welcome to join our private community which is a sanctuary for Sensitives. I created it based on recurring dreams I had about manifesting a school for x-men! People who feel, sense and experience the world in a unique way.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by مريم حسنا on July 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Make sure your definition of loyalty includes yourself. -maryam hasnaa'.

node.text:
Maybe you’re like me, someone with strong intuitive guidance, someone who sees the red flags and is able to astutely discern energies, but also someone for so long that had a distorted definition of loyalty that did not include my own self.

Last night for @newearthmysteryschool Energetic hygiene 2.0 class I got to teach all about this! 

I’m not interested in any framework that teaches you to have empathy for others and simultaneously none for yourself. It wasn’t until I addressed my trauma that I could even begin to understand what loyalty or true empathy was.

For many people growing up the person they loved and trusted the  most was also the same person they were most afraid of. And this is why so many struggle to discern the difference. 

I tune into what people mean not what they say. Sadly what most mean when they say “empathy“ is actually pity. Its a type of unskilled empathy that is extractive and reinforces a disempowered narrative. It leads to impulsive rescuing, self-abandonment and compromised integrity.

If you could embrace and release judgment about the part of you that tries to perform righteousness by over giving, people pleasing, self abandonment then the truth could be revealed. You could then see it’s safe to use discernment and have boundaries with how much you give of ourself.

We can't be naive in relationships or about the people we allow in our circle anymore. Be discerning with people who want blind loyalty but don’t have the basic skills to take ownership for harms, accountability for mistakes or the awareness of how to do the work to repair damage they have done to their relationships. These are all valid red flags.

Many times when I walk away from relationships it has nothing to do with being upset, mad, or unforgiving. It has to do with noticing the amount of emotional labor I would need to do based on that persons relationship blueprint and it just feels draining. I’m not teaching anyone how to be a good friend at this point in my life. We can always navigate personal preferences and boundaries. But if the basic skills of relating aren’t already in place, nothing personal, but it’s a no for me.

You can still catch the class btw!

node.text:
Daily energetic hygiene, psychic development and a consistent spiritual practice is what allows me to stay clear, authentic and in my own energy. 

I’ve done hundreds of energy healing sessions, workshops, classes, retreats and what I’ve found is that most people have a very difficult time staying in their body, focusing on themselves and having their own experience. Many times we jump into someone else’s space and absorb their energy. And we blame it on being Sensitive. Releasing others energy from our bodies is our birthright. 

If you’ve been following my work you know I specialize in training people who are highly sensitive, highly intuitive, clairvoyant, empathic and on rehabilitation from formerly identifying as Empaths. 

I created an Apothecary @vibrationalmedicine a school @newearthmysteryschool and a garden @theflowerpriestess specifically for this niche community. I created the exact thing for others that I wanted and needed when I was learning to navigate the world as an extremely Sensitive person. 

Most Sensitives, tend to spend a lot of time enmeshed with others. Our aura tends to be over extended, too diffused and our chakras tend to be too open in situations that are not aligned. 

This leads to this mindset I hear every day which is, I’m an Empath or I’m Sensitive and I can’t help absorbing other people’s energy. This is absolutely false information. And there are certain mindsets and belief systems that I just can not enable any longer. 

One of the main tools I train my students in is how to Own Our Space. To learn to discern, does this energy belong to me? This is a skill and a muscle that gives us closure and freedom. All types of intuition must be practiced the same way you would practice playing a musical instrument. This is especially true for Sensitives who require fine tuning. 

On Monday we have a guest, Cyndi Dale, author of The Subtle Body, Energetic Boundaries back for Energetic Hygiene Class. Next month we have my sister Tasha Nassar @tashabeee , fellow extra sensory as a guest for a conversation on The Highly Sensitive Intuitive in Relationships. Visit our school page for all the details. Link in bio!

node.text:
Many of us are past the point where a relationship can just be about attraction and romance. It actually has to be about liberation. 

I do the work so that I can awaken from the Dream not so that people will like me. 

I do the work to be a vessel, to gain access my memories, to reawaken to who I am, to discern truth from falsehood, to hear God, to release my soul from systems that want to drain my energy and siphon my life force. Not to be popular or on brand. 

Companionship is beautiful and sacred. Partnership is divine. Soul recognition is fun. Discovering new love languages is exciting. But let’s not get distracted here and forget the assignment. 

It doesn’t matter how much I love you, I can’t let anyone sabotage my mission. Always choose alignment with self over any sort of social currency.

As long as you’re being your authentic self, not being liked by certain people is literally a blessing.

node.text:
The beautiful thing about going through a phase where you purge, clear and heal old relationship patterns that are not aligned is that you move into a place where you manifest more soul to soul connections. Let me be clear, this purge is not a one time occurrence but an ongoing conversation. 

Relationships patterns will remain shallow when no one demands depth and substance from you. This is a manifestation of unspoken agreements to not being fully present and engaged in real connection. 

What I have learned is how to bring the focus back to myself at the appropriate times while in a relationship, I can let the other person off the hook. They are there to mirror, amplify and contribute to my happiness but there is no pressure to be the one responsible for my happiness. 

I’m so thankful that I can say to my loved ones....you are not responsible for my happiness(or my sadness), for feeling my feelings, for interpreting what I need, for transmuting my emotions, for doing my work or for completing me.
 
At this point, I’m not calling connections in because I feel anything is missing. I just enjoy having people to witness me and share my life with.

Check me and @soulisticwellness on “The WOO” with our sister @heyfranhey . Episode 4 and we are talking about buying into the dominant paradigm, pressure to conform, following our intuition, listening to our bodies, being ok with being misunderstood, slowing down and the courage it takes to fully shine! link to Frans Patreon Page in bio. 

Also we Are HIRING!

node.text:
This weekend we begin our class series on Energetic Hygiene. 

We will be talking about how to cleanse and clear our aura. 

Later this month we have Cyndi Dale, the author or Energetic Boundaries, back as our guest teacher. 

Setting subtle energetic boundaries helps you to choose to attune to your clarity, truth, and well being so you can be authentic to who you are. It is about not enmeshing, not merging and not allowing other people’s thoughts, emotions, judgements or projections into your field. 

That pattern of getting confused, dysregulated and overwhelmed by others emotional reactions to you prioritizing your own needs. Which results in second guessing yourself and then not being able to maintain or enforce your boundaries. That will need to eventually be addressed.

This is where many people get confused about what empathy actually is. When you merge with another person and lose a sense of individuation, you take on their feelings as your own. This is a pattern that has to be addressed in the nervous system and subtle body, not in the mental body. 

When we run false mental pictures of what empathy, compassion and caring is, it’s easy to have our desire to do the right thing be taken advantage of. But when we understand these things from an embodied place, we know them by how they feel. Even when others can’t see us clearly. 

Next month I will also be back at @ciis_sf @ciispubprograms teaching a workshop on Nature as a Spiritual Teacher. I’ll be shared how as a highly sensitive and Clairvoyant, working directly in collaboration with plant medicine and nature spirits has directed not only my healing journey but my own Spiritual path. I’ll be taking you on a journey as a seeker exploring the roadmap provided by various paths, paradigms, systems, lineages, and traditions about what it means to learn from nature and how we realistically do so. Which means we will be looking at these themes through various traditions including exploration of poetry from my own Sufi lineage. 

Join us. 
August 28, 2021
10:00 am to 5:00 pm

Link in bio.

node.text:
If you find yourself crying for no reason, that’s a good indicator that you are carrying other people’s grief in your space. And your body is trying its best to release it through tears.

If you are highly sensitive and or empathic and tend to just absorb other peoples energy I really strongly recommend learning energy work. It’s imperative to find the tools that support you being able to manage your sensitivity.

Often when we arrive at a certain level and can not go further it’s because there are shadow aspects that have to be honored, integrated and returned home before we can ascend more. Many of us are reuniting with parts of ourselves that we had to numb, tune out, ignore as it relates to seeing. We may have learned to turn off our sensitivity because we were overwhelmed and/or because we got in trouble for knowing stuff about people that they didn’t want anyone to know. 

As you ground, bring up the perfect frequency of Earth energy that validates you having a body. And that validates your ability as a Spirit to communicate guidance and intuitive information through the body as signals, impulses, feelings and sensations. That validates you as sensitive and how beautiful that is. 

I created my school @newearthmysteryschool and my plant apothecary @vibrationalmedicine specifically with Highly Sensitives in heart-mind. Because the support was not available for me as I navigated my sensitivity. But obviously you do not have to study with me. Just find a teacher, mentor or guide  that works for you.

I will never forgot the day I googled “what does it mean when you always feel worse around other people”. This was a defining moment because it was the moment I decided to do something about my experience as a Sensitive.

Join us on Sunday @newearthmysteryschool for Grounded Awareness 2.0. June 20th at 10 AM PDT

We are thrilled to have guest teacher @stevenwashingtonexperience Steven Washington! In this class, Steven will dive into mindful movement practices and grounding techniques.

There are so many spells, curses, illusions, distortions, veils, social agreements to conform and play the game right now that I honestly don’t even know where to start. 

I haven’t done an introduction so here we go. I was born Psychic, a transmedium and also highly sensitive. My environment as a child was very harsh and not supportive of my gifts so I turned them off. I spent most of my life thinking I was cursed because I couldn’t understand what was “wrong with me”. I have been having mystical experiences and seeing miracles since birth. I spent most of my early adulthood as an out of control psychic and an Empath. About ten years ago I retired as an empath and began training my gifts under some of the best Master Psychics, Clairvoyants and Healers. 

More about me: I am not here to make you comfortable or safe. I am not here to explain myself to you, to justify my life or my choices, to debate you on your opinions, to make adjustments and I’m not here to perform for you. Similar to your favorite DJ, I don’t take request. This ain’t -Build-a-spiritual-teacher. 

In my space, stop thinking you know everything or need to have an opinion on everything. Keep your well actuallys and bad faith arguments. Respectfully, your follow isn’t worth as much as you think it is. If you don’t agree with me or how I use my platform please cancel me. But leave the petty control dramas, manipulation tactics, psychic games and energy grabs for someone who doesn’t read and see energy. If I’m not for you, I’m not for you. If I don’t like your energy from jump, I’m blocking you, straight like that no questions asked. If you think this post seems out of character for me it’s only because you don’t actually know me. 

On a different note @newearthmysteryschool class is in session tonight 🤣😝 I’ll be teaching about grounding cords and how to ground energy. This will be a review for most of my students but a good time to refine your tools. For those new to energy work this is actually a good place to start. Link in bio to join. 

And if you want to see me at my happy place —-> @theflowerpriestess
